## Pool Model — Tenant Context in Spring Boot

```java
// Tenant context holder (ThreadLocal)
public class TenantContext {
    private static final ThreadLocal<String> TENANT = new ThreadLocal<>();

    public static void set(String tenantId) { TENANT.set(tenantId); }
    public static String get() { return TENANT.get(); }
    public static void clear() { TENANT.remove(); }
}

// Extract tenant from JWT / subdomain in filter
@Component
public class TenantFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {
    @Override
    protected void doFilterInternal(HttpServletRequest request,
                                    HttpServletResponse response,
                                    FilterChain chain) throws Exception {
        // Extract from subdomain: tenant-a.app.com
        String host = request.getServerName();
        String tenantId = host.split("\\.")[0];

        // Or extract from JWT claim
        // String tenantId = jwtUtil.extractClaim(token, "tenant_id");

        TenantContext.set(tenantId);
        try {
            chain.doFilter(request, response);
        } finally {
            TenantContext.clear(); // CRITICAL: prevent leaking
        }
    }
}
```

## Row-Level Security (Pool Model)

```java
// All queries automatically filtered by tenant_id
@Repository
public interface OrderRepository extends JpaRepository<Order, Long> {
    // Spring Data adds WHERE tenant_id = ? automatically via @Filter
    List<Order> findByStatus(OrderStatus status);
}

// Hibernate filter applied globally
@Entity
@FilterDef(name = "tenantFilter", 
           parameters = @ParamDef(name = "tenantId", type = String.class))
@Filter(name = "tenantFilter", condition = "tenant_id = :tenantId")
public class Order {
    @Column(name = "tenant_id")
    private String tenantId;
    // ...
}

// Enable filter for all queries in this session
@Aspect
@Component
public class TenantFilterAspect {
    @Autowired EntityManager em;

    @Before("execution(* com.example.repository.*.*(..))")  
    public void enableFilter() {
        Session session = em.unwrap(Session.class);
        session.enableFilter("tenantFilter")
               .setParameter("tenantId", TenantContext.get());
    }
}
```

## Bridge Model — Dynamic Datasource Routing

```java
// Each tenant gets its own DB schema/database
@Component
public class TenantDataSourceRouter extends AbstractRoutingDataSource {
    @Override
    protected Object determineCurrentLookupKey() {
        return TenantContext.get(); // routes to tenant's datasource
    }
}

@Configuration
public class DataSourceConfig {
    @Bean
    public DataSource dataSource(TenantDataSourceRouter router) {
        Map<Object, Object> dataSources = new HashMap<>();
        dataSources.put("tenant-a", buildDataSource("jdbc:postgresql://host/tenant_a"));
        dataSources.put("tenant-b", buildDataSource("jdbc:postgresql://host/tenant_b"));
        router.setTargetDataSources(dataSources);
        router.afterPropertiesSet();
        return router;
    }
}
```
